Revision history for App-CPAN2Pkg

3.004     2014-06-12 14:04:24+02:00 Europe/Paris
 - urls shouldn't have newlines (gh#4)

3.003     2014-04-04 14:34:35+02:00 Europe/Paris
 - fix Moose enum warning
 - make it work with dzil v5
 - add env var CPAN2PKG_NO_CPANP_X to skip "cpanp x"

3.002     2012-10-29 13:47:56 Europe/Paris
 - mageia: allow only 2 urpm instances at the same time to prevent fork pikes

3.001     2012-10-09 13:51:44 Europe/Paris
 - tk ui: allow user to mark a module as available
 - tk ui: prevent empty module creation
 - tk ui: "clean all" button now below the hlist

3.000     2012-10-09 11:08:45 Europe/Paris
 - moving to dzpba-jquelin 3.x
 - mageia: waiting only 1 minute for index (bs now pauses by itself)
 - mageia: prevent warning when bs ate the submission
 - prereqs: prevent Module::AutoInstall to kick in
 - text ui: clearer internal cpan2pkg information

**

2.122690  2012-09-25 15:51:35 Europe/Paris
 - new text interface available

2.122620  2012-09-18 13:44:38 Europe/Paris
 - using official (yet hidden) mageia bs api instead of parsing html

2.120460  2012-02-15 09:39:46 Europe/Paris
 - fix pod name of bin/cpan2pkg

2.120370  2012-02-06 09:53:42 Europe/Paris
 - reflect new page layout of pkgsubmit.mageia.org

2.111781  2011-06-27 17:28:44 Europe/Paris
 - adding missing prereq POE::Loop::Tk, not autodetected

2.111780  2011-06-27 14:40:26 Europe/Paris
 - using dist::zilla for release: versioning is 2.YYDDDN (YY=year,
   DDD=day of year, N=increment in case of multiple releases per day)
 - using a tk gui instead of a curses one
 - mageia platform fully supported
 - platform mandriva no more supported (can be adapted quite easily)

**

1.1.0 Sat Jun  6 20:27:53 CEST 2009
 - using cpan2dist --ban instead of --ignore, which somehow seems to have changed
 - adding resources to meta.yml

1.0.0 Sun May 17 12:14:19 CEST 2009
 - updating prereqs + moving on when module installed from upstream
 - splitted module in poe session + worker
 - moved info from app:cpan2pkg to module attributes
 - don't submit on upstream build-system if missing prereqs on it
 - cpan2pkg documentation written

